<br>
There are a number of good choices: Kael, Chardok, The Hole, City of Mist....  However given the level of our members and considering the levels of our friends in ToA,along with the limited raiding most of our members have done,  two of these stand out as better choices, Kael and City of Mist.<br>
<br>
Kael is the city of the Frost Giants. the armor pieces that drop there are referred to as Thurg armor, it is very nice armor for all but the real high end raiding. It does not drop fast though, so a raid might get one or two pieces, or even none if unlucky.  Kael is also the land of faction!  great CoV faction hits, whereas a drakkel wolf in GD will get you a single point of faction, the giants are anywhere from 5 to 100 points worth of CoV faction.  The best drops and faction are from the giants in the Arena.<br>
<br>
City of Mist has been taken over by the dead and undead. the object of our raid there would be the dreaded Dark Reavers.  They are tough, like to hang out together, have lots of friends, and on accassion respawn on the spot they die. BUT they drop the jade Reavers, needed for both the druid and ranger epics.<br>
<br>
Both of these raids, to really succeed, need one thing we do not have, a 55+ monk.  <br>
<br>
Outside of that, both are good choices. With Kael being the easier to recover from a wipe.<br>
<br>
So let me know, via replying to this message what you want the next raid to be, and why.<br>
<br>
Gloro Lisk<br>
